  "body": "I saw a mixing which implemented render something like this:\n\n```\nrender: function(){\n  return this.pureRender(this.props, this.state);\n}\n```\n\nThe user then had to implement a `pureRender(props, state)` function.\nTo me, it seems like a nice hack and I'm wondering why this isn't the default way of React? Any thoughts?\n",
